    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="767"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">737.56/5–151</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chief of the Lend-Lease and Surplus Property
                        Staff</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Meigs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the Division of Investments,
                        Bureau of Accounts, Treasury Department</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-01">May 1,
                            1951</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Barnes</hi>: There are being transmitted to the
                    Treasury Department, Division of Investments, by this Department, two
                    remittances aggregating $335,329.46 for credit to the Cuban lend-lease accounts
                    on your books. One of these is a draft on the National City Bank of New York by
                    its Habana branch, payable to the Treasurer of the United States in the sum of
                        $214,988.04;<note n="1" xml:id="d767fn1">A check to this amount from the
                        Cuban Government was delivered by Ambassador Machado to Secretary Acheson at
                        the Department of State on April 27 (737.56/4–2751).</note> the other, in
                    the sum of $120,341.42, represents a transfer of a credit accruing to Cuba as
                    the result of the completion of accounting on certain interim arms program
                    contracts.</p>
                <p>The total residual lend-lease indebtedness of Cuba is $335,329.46 as follows:
                        <table cols="2" rows="2">
                        <row>
                            <cell>Balance due under “treaty” terms</cell>
                            <cell role="num">$300,767.23</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Balance due on “cash” account</cell>
                            <cell role="num">34,562.23</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>
                <p>Therefore, the completion of these credit transactions will fully liquidate the
                    monetary responsibility of the Government of Cuba under the Lend-Lease Agreement
                    of November 7, 1941.<note n="2" xml:id="d767fn2">For text of the United
                        States-Cuba Lend-Lease Agreement, signed at Washington, November 7, 1941,
                        and entered into force on the same date, see <ref
                            target="frus1941v07#pg_122">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">vii</hi>, p. 122</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Your confirmation will be appreciated.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carroll M. Meigs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
